      • getRows

        public java.util.List getRows()
        If the LisaJdbcInterceptor has been configured and LISA is active, result sets will be included in the integrator object.
        Returns:
        a list of XML strings with element names matching the table & column names and the string values of the attributes is xml-friendly text. The order of the list is the order which ResultSet.next() was called. e.g. 
                 
        
         String 0: <row><FIRSTNAME>Bart</USER.FIRSTNAME><LASTNAME>Simpson</LASTNAME></row> 
        
         String 1: <row><FIRSTNAME>Lisa</FIRSTNAME><LASTNAME>Simpson</LASTNAME></row>

        If the original query joined two or more tables, the table name will be prepended to the column name, e.g. "USERS.FIRSTNAME, "ADDRESS.ZIP".

        If the query used anonymous column names, e.g. "select age+1 from users where name = 'itko'" then the column name will be 'anonymousColumn'
